  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Sir</p>
            <p>i am sorry to inform you that we cannot procure a room for your lectures: the reason is we have had some lectures deliver[e]d here, lately on Socialism, which have so alarm'd our Clerical and Parochial functionaries that they have threatened and intimidated eve[r]y Innkeeper. to remedy this evil we the Free-Thinkers have in contemplation to build a "Hall of Science", which being built by the Infidel will be devoted to all subjects and Sciences having for their object [[2]] the emancipation of Mankind from the dominion of a sectarian Priesthood.</p>
            <p>may that Noble, Independent, Pioneering spirit which is so superlatively yours never rest untill you see yourself crown[e]d with success an that you  may enjoy health and long life in the ardent wish of yours in the cause of Science [versus??] Theology.</p>
            <p>Jon[atha]n Aldam</p>
      </body>
